-- East African Portland Slides to Full-Year Loss, Sees Improved 2011 Results
-- B y   V e r n o n   W e s s e l s
-- 2010-10-06T06:33:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-06/east-african-portland-slides-to-full-year-loss-sees-improved-2011-results.html
East African Portland Cement Ltd.
posted a net loss of 292.4 million shillings in the year through
June 30 compared with a year-earlier profit of 1.83 billion
shillings, the Nairobi-based cement producer said.  Fiscal full-year sales rose to 9.41 billion shillings from
8.1 billion shillings a year earlier, it said in a statement
distributed today by the Nairobi Stock Exchange.  It didn’t
declare a dividend.  “Market demand for cement remains strong and the company
expects improved production and sales volumes in the coming
year,” East African Portland Cement said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Vernon Wessels at 
 vwessels@bloomberg.net  